HEADWORD: Casuarinales
<hw>Casuarinales</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>an order of chiefly Australian
trees and shrubs comprising the casuarinas, having only one family,
<fam>Casuarinaceae</fam>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> order <ord>Casuarinales</ord>.</syn>⟦br⟧
